==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Czech
<hw>Czech</hw> <pr>(ch⟦ecr⟧k; 204)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One of the Czechs; an inhabitant or native of the <country>Czech
Republic</country>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The language of the Czechs (often called Bohemian),
the harshest and richest of the Slavic languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
<country>Czechoslovakia</country> or the <country>Czech
Republic</country>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Czechic</ent>⟦br⟧
